An example would be Annie vs. Yasuo. Annie has a fantastic possible 5-man stun, but one that requires cycling through spells and holding it until the right moment. The CD and circumstances to hit the game-changing flash-tibbers are long enough that while it is not necessarily a difficult shot to land, the fact that you had it up at the right time shows patience and foresight.

Yasuo, on the other hand, has a potential 5-man knockup/extra hangtime on a very short cooldown for the utility (I believe 23s at max rank). Unlike Annie, this one is hard to hit more than one person with, and as such there are more opportunities to do so. Yasuo, as a more mechanically focused champion, is more reliant on landing a skillshot, and rarely has to hold anything like Annie does.

